data.event: The borough is coterminous with New York County, founded on November 1, 1683 as one of the state's original counties.

data.event: Historically documented to have been purchased by Dutch colonists from Native Americans in 1626, for the equivalent of US$1050, Manhattan real estate has since become among the most expensive in the world, with the value of Manhattan Island, including real estate, estimated to exceed US$3 trillion in 2013.
